original_sentence: Before installation, first, ensure you have a recent version of Python and pip, then clone the repository using the `--sparse` option: ```bash git clone --sparse git@github.com:dylanashley/story-distiller.git ```  Afterwards, install the Python dependencies using pip: ```bash pip install -r requirements.txt ```  To use the full suite of file types supported by the tool, it is also necessary to separately install the [ffmpeg](https://ffmpeg.org/) tool by following the instructions for your operating system provided on [their website](https://ffmpeg.org/download.html).
